documentation.text:
@dev Contract for maintaining organization registry
 Contract inherits from Ownable and ERC165Compatible
 Ownable contains ownership criteria of the organization registry
 ERC165Compatible contains interface compatibility checks

@dev constructor function that takes the address of a pre-deployed ERC1820
 registry. Ideally, this contract is a publicly known address:
 0x1820a4B7618BdE71Dce8cdc73aAB6C95905faD24. Inherently, the constructor
 sets the interfaces and registers the current contract with the global registry

registerInterfaces(bytes32,address,addre.details: Function to register an organization's interfaces for easy lookup

params._groupName: name of the working group registered by an organization
params._shieldAddress: name of the registered shield registry interface
params._tokenAddress: name of the registered token interface
params._verifierAddress: name of the verifier registry interface

returns._0: `true` upon successful registration of the organization's interfaces

params._whisperKey: public key required for message communication
params._zkpPublicKey: public key required for commitments & to verify EdDSA signatures with

returns._0: `true` upon successful registration of the organization
